{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:29:04.280Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Embedding visualization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of using dimensionality reduction techniques like "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to project high-dimensional embeddings into 2D or 3D space so humans can visually explore structure, clusters, and relationships in the data."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “Visualization techniques like t-SNE, UMAP, and Nomic Atlas help you "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "project these high-dimensional embeddings into 2D space for easy exploration on a flat surface"}, {"type": "text", "text": ".”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Embedding Visualization — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What is an embedding?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "An "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "embedding"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a numeric representation of data in a high-dimensional vector space, where:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Similar items have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "similar vectors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (close in the space)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dissimilar items have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "different vectors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (far apart)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Examples:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Word embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": each word is a vector (e.g., 300 dimensions) capturing semantic similarity"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Document embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": each document is a vector representing its meaning"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Image embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": each image is a vector capturing visual features"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "User/item embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": in recommendation systems"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "These embeddings are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "not human-readable"}, {"type": "text", "text": " directly because they’re in high-dimensional space (e.g., 128, 256, 300, 1024 dimensions)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why visualize embeddings?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Embedding visualization helps you:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Understand what the model learned"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- See if similar concepts cluster together - Check if the embedding space is structured meaningfully"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Discover clusters and patterns"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Identify natural groupings (e.g.,词 classes, topics, user types) - Spot outliers or anomalies"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Debug and validate models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Check if embeddings separate classes well - Detect data quality issues or label noise"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Communicate results"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Create intuitive visualizations for stakeholders - Show how the model organizes data"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Explore data before building models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Understand the structure of your data - Inform feature engineering or model choices"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How t-SNE and UMAP work for embedding visualization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both t-SNE and UMAP are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "nonlinear dimensionality reduction"}, {"type": "text", "text": " methods that preserve local structure, making them ideal for embedding visualization."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "t-SNE for embeddings"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Converts high-dimensional distances into "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "probabilities"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Gaussian)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Defines a low-dimensional distribution using a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Student t-distribution"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimizes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "KL divergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between the two distributions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Strengths"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Very clear, tight "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "clusters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Excellent for showing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "local neighborhoods"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weaknesses"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - Distorts "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "global structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (distances between clusters meaningless) - Slow on large datasets"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "UMAP for embeddings"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Builds a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "high-dimensional graph"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of nearest neighbors (k-NN)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Models data as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fuzzy topological structure"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Finds a low-dimensional embedding that preserves this graph via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cross-entropy"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Strengths"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Preserves "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "more global structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": " than t-SNE - Much "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "faster"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and scalable to large datasets - Supports "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "out-of-sample transform"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (embed new points)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Weaknesses"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - Slightly less tight clusters than t-SNE in some cases"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": t-SNE and UMAP applied to word embeddings from 19th-century literature.\n---"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical workflow for embedding visualization"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Train or obtain embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Word embeddings (e.g., from Word2Vec, BERT) - Document embeddings (e.g., from transformer models) - Image embeddings (e.g., from CNNs) - Latent space from autoencoders"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Extract vectors"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Get the embedding matrix (N × d, where N is number of items, d is embedding dimension)"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Apply dimensionality reduction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "```python from sklearn.manifold import TSNE from umap import UMAP"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# t-SNE tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=30) embedding_2d = tsne.fit_transform(embeddings)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# UMAP umap = UMAP(n_neighbors=20, min_dist=0.3, metric='correlation') embedding_2d = umap.fit_transform(embeddings) # [] ```"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Plot in 2D/3D"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Use scatter plots (matplotlib, seaborn, plotly) - Color by labels, categories, or metadata - Example: clustering of myeloid, T-cells, cancer, B-cells, epithelial cells\n5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpret"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": - Look for clusters - Check if semantic groups separate - Identify outliers or mixed regions"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Embedding visualization in Classical ML vs. Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Classical Machine Learning"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used for:"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exploring"}, {"type": "text", "text": " word embeddings, document embeddings - Visualizing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "latent representations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from autoencoders - Understanding "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cluster structure"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in high-dimensional data\n- Purpose: - Data exploration - Debugging models - Understanding feature spaces"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Used for:"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Visualizing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LLM embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., token embeddings from BERT, GPT) - Understanding "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "latent spaces"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in diffusion models, GANs - Exploring "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "user/item embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in recommendation systems\n- Purpose: - Debugging and improving generative models - Understanding how models organize knowledge - Explaining model behavior to stakeholders"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In both cases, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE and UMAP"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are the go-to tools for making embeddings interpretable."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Embedding visualization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " uses t-SNE and UMAP to project high-dimensional embeddings into 2D/3D so humans can see structure, clusters, and relationships."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It helps you "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "understand what models learned"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "discover patterns"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "debug models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "communicate results"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE"}, {"type": "text", "text": " excels at clear, tight local clusters; "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is faster, preserves more global structure, and supports new data."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "classical ML"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", it’s used for exploring embeddings and latent spaces; in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generative AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", it’s used for visualizing LLM embeddings, latent spaces, and model behavior."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The workflow is: get embeddings → apply t-SNE/UMAP → color and plot → interpret clusters and structure."}]}]}]}]}}